      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "JxAuP-foRKTa7SDleFM1d"
      ],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 51,
      "version": 104,
      "versionNonce": 1568461149,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774528205482,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "architecture idea\n1) partner-facing and internal systems are split by a strict\nedge layer.\n2) integration is contract-first: every payload has schema,\nversion, and idempotency key.\n3) core is event-driven to decouple channels from business\nlogic.\n4) analytics consumes the same events to keep business\nand BI consistent.\n\ncore principles\n- zero direct exposure of internal services\n- least privilege and tenant isolation\n- exactly-once semantics at business level (idempotent\ncommands)\n- replayability: any failed stream can be replayed\n- end-to-end observability with trace IDs\n- data governance: PII tags, retention, lineage\n\nmicro architecture moments\n- token + certificate rotation is automated\n- outbox pattern for reliable event publishing\n- DLQ handling with manual/auto replay policy\n- schema evolution with backward compatibility checks\n- per-partner quotas and circuit breakers\n- SLO gates in CI/CD before release",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "architecture idea\n1) partner-facing and internal systems are split by a strict edge layer.\n2) integration is contract-first: every payload has schema, version, and idempotency key.\n3) core is event-driven to decouple channels from business logic.\n4) analytics consumes the same events to keep business and BI consistent.\n\ncore principles\n- zero direct exposure of internal services\n- least privilege and tenant isolation\n- exactly-once semantics at business level (idempotent commands)\n- replayability: any failed stream can be replayed\n- end-to-end observability with trace IDs\n- data governance: PII tags, retention, lineage\n\nmicro architecture moments\n- token + certificate rotation is automated\n- outbox pattern for reliable event publishing\n- DLQ handling with manual/auto replay policy\n- schema evolution with backward compatibility checks\n- per-partner quotas and circuit breakers\n- SLO gates in CI/CD before release",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 624,
      "index": "an",
      "frameId": null,
      "autoResize": false
    },
    {
      "id": "legend",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1840,
      "y": 907.9999999999999,
